mdElement.text: These projects use massively the maven plugin Each xxx-spec project contains a UML model. The xxx-api, xxx-impl projects are generated by a set of templates.

A Generic Expression Language The implementation is supposed to be used in place of JSR 341 expression language
The specification is based on Object Constraint Language specification http://www.omg.org/spec/OCL/2.4/PDF

An execution language defined as a subset of Action Language for Foundational UML (Alf) specification http://www.omg.org/spec/ALF/1.1
xlang stand for eXecution LANGuage
Classes in this package read OCL (Gel) expressions and build various sets of xlang statements
The ete-maven-plugin facilitates the use of the library through a maven process.

The purpose of the whole project is to run an mda process. The core of the project is the ete-lib subproject. This project defines a process through pipelines of actions. Each action takes an eventual model on entry and returns a model.
This diagram shows the very first layer : these packages enable embedding mda processes into a standard Java process
Each package is materialized as a (sub)project
Implementation of dynamic versions of Visitor and AbstractFactory design patterns Actually, this is not a subproject of ete but a standalone project.
Contains an adapter for the JSR 341 language
